	<Title>
		Are leg cramps disturbing your sleep?
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Leg cramps are most common during rest or sleep. To prevent leg cramps, stretch your calves and feet for a few minutes before bedtime. Or take a few spins on your stationary bike. It may also help to wear shoes that have proper support and drink plenty of fluids during the day.&lt;/p&gt;
